        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-11-06T15:33:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "sklog.FmtErrorf should probably be moved to a different package because it has nothing to do with logging. It\u0027s basically the same as fmt.Errorf but it adds a stacktrace to the error.",
      "parentUuid": "5cb3d569_03322cf1",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 2007,
        "startChar": 16,
        "endLine": 2007,
        "endChar": 25
      },
      "revId": "92f6697e538fcdc739be05ac598a7f452f682501",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "49e4d91f_263a79d7",
        "filename": "task_scheduler/go/scheduling/task_scheduler.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 2079,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-11-06T14:53:10Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We\u0027re actually leaking the metric here.  Rather than setting its value to zero and letting it hang around, we should Delete() it.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 2078,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 2079,
        "endChar": 15
      },
      "revId": "92f6697e538fcdc739be05ac598a7f452f682501",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "30b09d3c_2ff71432",
        "filename": "task_scheduler/go/scheduling/task_scheduler.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 2079,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-11-06T15:33:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "If we immediately delete, then the 0 won\u0027t be sent to Prometheus, so the old value sticks around. If the previous value was causing an alert, the alert will stay active indefinitely. I could try to figure out how to delete it after the next cycle, but IMO the severity of this leak is pretty small.",
      "parentUuid": "49e4d91f_263a79d7",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 2078,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 2079,
        "endChar": 15
      },
      "revId": "92f6697e538fcdc739be05ac598a7f452f682501",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "972da120_098bc711",
        "filename": "task_scheduler/go/scheduling/task_scheduler.go",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 2079,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-11-06T15:39:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "IIUC we always query over a time range (ie. last N seconds/minutes/etc), as opposed to the last data point regardless of timestamp, so the alert should only stay around as long as the specified time window.  I agree that writing the zero will cause the alert to disappear immediately which is the desired behavior, and I agree that the leak is probably not severe enough to worry about given the low rate of job name turnover.",
      "parentUuid": "30b09d3c_2ff71432",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 2078,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 2079,
        "endChar": 15
      },
      "revId": "92f6697e538fcdc739be05ac598a7f452f682501",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
